name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: io.file.buffer.size
description:
The size of buffer for use in sequence files.
  The size of this buffer should probably be a multiple of hardware
  page size (4096 on Intel x86), and it determines how much data is
  buffered during read and write operations.

name: dfs.datanode.socket.write.timeout
description: Timeout in ms for clients socket writes to DataNodes.

name: dfs.namenode.replication.max-streams
description: Hard limit for the number of replication streams other than those with highest-priority.

name: ha.health-monitor.sleep-after-disconnect.ms
description: How long to sleep after an unexpected RPC error.

name: dfs.namenode.edekcacheloader.initial.delay.ms
description:
When KeyProvider is configured, the time delayed until the first
    attempt to warm up edek cache on NN start up / become active.

name: dfs.block.misreplication.processing.limit
description: Maximum number of blocks to process for initializing replication queues.
